ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Very useful documents class for pre-modern China.
If one wishes to conduct research in pre-morden Chinese history, this course is a must.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: Very useful preparation for working with pre-modern sources on China. However, this is only a start, much more work ahead that no graduate seminar can prepare one for.
Without this course, I would not really understand how to use different types of pre-mordern Chinese sources.
